  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The navigation bar uses `CommunityButton` to render tab icon buttons. `CommunityButton` is really just a variation of `StatusIconTabButton`, but it still needs some decoupling. \r\n\r\nThe main differences are:\r\n\r\n- It comes with a tooltip to render a community name\r\n- it has an optional badge for rendering a message count\r\n\r\nWe should:\r\n- Move it into component library and ideally come up with a better name for it. It's a `StatusIconTabButton` that can have a badge and a tooltip, that's nothing necessarily specific to communities\r\n- Remove anything that's community related (`chatsModel`, constants etc)",
